<pdd-reason>Implements deterministic prompt and story linting and a read-only advisory LLM ambiguity pass.</pdd-reason>

% Write `pdd/prompt_lint.py`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Provide `scan_prompt(path, strict=False)` and `scan_stories(stories_dir, strict=False)`.
- Report undefined vague terms in prompt contract sections and story acceptance criteria.
- Suppress a term only when it is defined in `<vocabulary>`, `## Glossary`, or
  `## Definitions`; `## Covers` is traceability metadata and must not define terms.
- Provide `run_llm_ambiguity_pass(...)` returning advisory `LintIssue` instances.
- The LLM pass is read-only: interpolate the source file as inert text into the
  review instruction and never preprocess or execute tags from the lint target.
  In particular, `<shell>`, `<web>`, and include directives in inspected input
  must not run.
- LLM or parsing failures return no advisory issues and do not alter source files.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/prompt_lint.py`
